  "prompt": "What countries can I travel to without an Indian passport?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff date in October 2023, Indian citizens require a passport to travel internationally. However, there are certain countries and regions where Indian citizens can enter without a visa or obtain a visa on arrival, but a passport is still a fundamental requirement for international travel.\n\nA passport is an essential travel document issued by a country to its citizens that confirms their identity and nationality. It is necessary for entering and leaving countries, and for most international travel activities, including boarding a flight. \n\nSo regardless of the travel destination, an Indian passport is necessary for:\n\n1. Boarding international flights or ships.\n2. Passing through border controls.\n3. Validating identity and nationality in foreign countries to access services, rentals, hotels, and other travel-related activities.\n\nEven within countries that have visa-free or visa-on-arrival agreements with India, Indian citizens must carry and present a valid Indian passport for entry.\n\nIf you mean traveling domestically within India, no passport is required, and other forms of identification, such as an Aadhar card, driver's license, or voter ID, can be used.\n\nFor the most current and accurate travel-related advice, including passport and visa requirements, always check the destination country's official government or immigration website, or consult with travel authorities.",
